<h1>Problem 1208 - 2013 IMO, P1 of 6, N</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Assume that \(k\) and \(n\) are two positive integers. Prove that there exist positive integers \(m_1 , \dots , m_k\) such that \[1+\frac{2^k-1}{n}=\left(1+\frac1{m_1}\right)\cdots \left(1+\frac1{m_k}\right).\]</p>
